## Workflow SOP

**Lifecycle**: `vibe init` → `vibe start` → work → `vibe sync` → repeat → `vibe sync --close`

### Checkpoint Rule (automatic, no human command needed)
After completing each task in `state/tasks.md`:
1. Mark it `[x]` in `state/tasks.md`.
2. Append one-line progress to `state/current.md`.

**Task completion means**: code written AND verified (tests pass, or manual confirmation from the human). Do not mark `[x]` if the code is untested.

### Reality-First Principle
When your memory conflicts with git, **git is the absolute truth**. Verify with `git status`/`git diff`/`git log` before writing to state files. If git history was force-pushed, ask the human before trusting it.

### Empty State Handling
If `state/current.md` or `state/tasks.md` is empty or missing, ask the human for context before proceeding. Do not invent tasks or fabricate progress.

## Standards
- Conventional Commits. One logical change per commit.
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, or passwords. Use `.env` files.

## Boundaries — Prohibited Actions
These rules have NO exceptions unless the human explicitly overrides:
- **Do NOT** execute destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git reset --hard`, `git push --force`, `DROP TABLE`, `docker system prune`, or any command that deletes data) without explicit human confirmation.
- **Do NOT** modify `.vibe/config.toml` or `.vibe/state/.lifecycle`. These are managed by the `vibe` CLI only.
- **Writing to `state/tasks.md` and `state/current.md` per the Checkpoint Rule IS permitted.**
- **Do NOT** exfiltrate project data to external services, URLs, or third-party APIs.
- **Do NOT** delete or overwrite files outside the project directory.
- **Do NOT** fabricate test results or claim code works without verifiable evidence (terminal output, test logs, or API responses).

## Context Files
- `state/current.md` — latest progress snapshot (read at every session start)
- `state/tasks.md` — task checklist (mark `[x]` when done, never delete items)
- `state/architecture.md` — tech stack and design decisions
- `state/standards.md` — coding conventions
- `state/experiments.md` — autoresearch experiment history (auto-populated by `vibe sync`)
- `state/archive.md` — cold storage (read only when you need historical context)

## Autoresearch Integration
This project supports [autoresearch](https://github.com/uditgoenka/autoresearch) experiment loops.
- Experiment commits (prefixed `autoresearch:` or `[autoresearch]`) are auto-detected by `vibe sync`
- Results are recorded in `state/experiments.md` with KEPT/REVERTED status
- `vibe start` shows experiment summary
- Use `/autoresearch` in Claude Code to run optimization loops; vibe handles the memory
